\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-490\li518\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid2690112 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3949159\charrsid874358 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 You were about to tell me about a job that your husband was going to do?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Oh - at - at the German family. That was in the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}West End{\*\xmlclose}
 somewhere. And - the war broke out. And - there was no - well they went for the - thinking they were going - had got employment they found no one there. Well they thought the best thing for them to do, he and his 
friends that was in the trade - was to join up as tradesmen in the army. And my word, was it a fight. People were - the men were just fighting each other to join up. Had their collars torn off them and - it was really a rough time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Did you see it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 I didn't see it. But he did of course, he was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Did he tell you about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 
He told me about when - he got home. Well - a day or two after that, they had a - papers come through, and they'd only joined for during the war. But on the papers t
hey received they were put down as regular servicemen, which naturally they did not want, they only wanted duration of the war, and - this night my husband was very restless and I couldn't make out what was wrong, he hadn't told me - told my mother that l
i
ved next door - and - in the morning they all made - he and his friends - went back to the War Office, and luckily they got it put right because - being a tradesman they got more money you see, it was twenty-eight shillings a week. And - when he came home
, he naturally told me why he was so worried. But that was put right of course. Well then he was sta - stationed at various places in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Somerset{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and - around which I was able - not having a family, to - stay with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 You followed him round did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Yes. And - we were in - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Somerset{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} when they finally moved off to France, and I always remember those lorries going off - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}France
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. I can always see them. And - he was there - of course until the war ended, but the were - some happy times in between when he g
ot leave. Wed had a raid, I was took on at - a job at a cinema, because it took the weekends up, and - occupied - myself for the weekend as well as the week, and - this morn - Saturday morning the ladies used to do the dusting and as the men had been - ca
l
led up there was only one elderly man that used to do the hovering, so we ladies used to do the dusting. And this raid started. And on the way home and when I got home to the flat I was in then, I was upset and I said well if - my husband doesn't get kill
ed I will.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 You really felt that did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 
And - there's only me of course others. And - went back to - the cinema in the afternoon. Was busy - walking round with the chocolate tray and someone called out Mrs Hall}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13595585\charrsid1710208 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 m, here's your husband. And God, that was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 He was just there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 
He - he'd been phoning cinemas, he knew I was - you know, where - I should be but he'd got the wrong - address, and he was worried, they'd heard about the raid, and - I'd put my holiday off and - having the news
 that he would be home - at some time, and - of course it was lovely to - see him, and the manager of the cinema said, now Mrs Hallam, you'll like your holiday. So off we went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Brighton{\*\xmlclose}
 the next - day, for his leave after he'd seen his parents and mine. So that was a happy time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Did you stay in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Brighton{\*\xmlclose}
 in a boarding house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Then he went back again to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}France{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} did he after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 
Oh yes. Yes. He went back and was there - he never got another leave after that, and he was there until th
e war ended. And - I - had a letter - oh he was - ill, and - I was still at the cinema, and he'd got to - Waterloo station, through a card out the window, and that found me, my landlady's daughter brought the card to me at the cinema and when I read it he
 was on his way to a hospital - and did not know where, and he finished up - oh miles away, now where was that? Oh dear, can't - think where that was now. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} I think. Yes. And my mother and I went off the next morning - to visit him. And - he did re
cover of course, there. And we managed to - get a room, in a cottage. And he wasn't supposed to come home at night but he did. The - other chaps used to make the bed up as if he was there. And - one morning he - was going off 'cos he used to get up about 
f
ive to get back. And - there was a dog - he would go out the back way, climbing a fence and caught his trousers in the wire. Tore them. And - but he wasn't, you know, in any trouble at all over it. I don't know if his officer ever knew. Well then - he was
 
discharged from there, and also the war ended, which was - very nice. And - I went - was staying - went to see mother and said that I was expecting - my husband home any time. I said, I think I'd better go home now in case. And he was - he'd arrived there
 and was getting ready to come to me, he guessed where I'd be. So of course that was lovely when the war ended. And - of course that meant finding - work again which was very precarious, and there was a strike on in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} soon after that. At - a new buildi
ng that was going up, and - my husband was a trades unionist, I don't know how you feel about - or your husband feels about them. Well it was necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Do you not like unions yourself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Oh yes, I was with him all the way. Well - well of course. 
Yes. Yes. Well he - he'd been in the - trades union for - so many years, I can't really - remember how many, and - evidently these men that was - kept on at this firm - oh it was so - I wish I could think of the name of the building. Some important buildi
n
g going on, and they went - the union officials went to see these men - these men, and said if only they'd - hold out - they would - pay their - wages whatever they'd got to come, but of course it would come out of the - union's money. Through that they g
ot discharged from the union. And if ever a man was broken he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 A terrible shock was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 
Yes. After all the years and the work he'd put in. But - some years after that they sent him a letter as an honorary member which - we never thought anything of at all. Because it didn't seem worth them bothering.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 What was the name of his union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 
Electrical Trade Union. And - of course after a while he settled down and found we were - happy because we'd got more time for us at home, and - he built h
imself an aviary then and bred canaries and - he realized you know that life was - is freer for him, without a lot of worry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Was he very interested in trade unionism when you first met him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Well no, not until he came home from the fourteen war. T
hat taught him a lot. He went in almost a boy. But when he came home from the war he'd seen a lot of things and how people made money during war, through wars, on ammunitions and things, he was a changed man that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Was he also active in the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Oh yes. We both were, mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Was your own family a Labour family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 
Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Well I mean when you've struggled so - it - opens your eyes doesn't it to things. Well even on - there the other night I know there's a lot of vanda
lism goes on to - today, but - a man said, we put millions in their pockets, now it's our turn, and I thought how right you are. Oh I'm still - very up with it. Well - my husband thought - about buying a house, and - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}
}Surrey{\*\xmlclose} he thought was the best place as
 the council there lent the money. Well I was walking down the street with my two children and a gipsy stopped me and she couldn't have known the house I came out of, is this - what you want? And - and naturally she wanted me to buy something which I didn
'
t. She said to me you're moving from here - as of course I knew I was and I never said to her I was. And she said - you'll be very happy, but, she said, you'll have something happen, but you'll get over it and you'll be ve - quite happy where you're going
.
 And bother me, we moved there in the November, and my husband met with an accident in the March. And he was home for six months. And that - was her answer, and was what she'd told me. But - luckily for him - he had his wages, which we never thought he wo
