Oh no, we were - oh, the first war we were still at Highgate, I was living next door to - my mother. And of course I had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 Could you just tell me, that place in Upper Holloway,
 how long did you stay on there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9966907 H  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 
Well - the - people that - had the house, the landlady - landlord, they - took - it's rather a big house, and - we had the top - flat, of it, of this house, and we were only there a - I don't think it could have been a
 year, and her husband evidently they found - in those days although - he was attached to the church and used to work for - the church, I don't know actually what his job was. But in those days he used to go to business in a top hat. And - they - evidentl
y with the - they also let a flat underneath - we - our flat, and - they couldn't - carry on with the house, so - we all had to move. So we were there I suppose - about eleven months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2690112 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3949159\charrsid1710208 What was your next home then?
